CAPE TOWN - Standard Bank Proteas opening batsman, Hashim Amla, has been rested for the final Momentum One-Day International (ODI) against Bangladesh taking place at Buffalo Park in East London on Sunday. Amla has been in prolific form in both the Test and ODI series against Bangladesh, with an aggregate of 492 runs in two Tests and two ODIs including three consecutive centuries. READ: CSA congratulates Proteas on series victory Amla has been replaced by Proteas Test opener, Aiden Markram, who has earned his maiden ODI call-up following a successful Test debut. The Proteas lead the series 2-0.  
	The squad will travel to East London on Thursday ahead of the final match of the series. African News Agency